All Progressives Congress (APC) stalwart Asiwaju Bola Ahmed Tinubu yesterday hosted the leadership of the United Kingdom (UK) chapter of the party and the Nigeria Diaspora for Asiwaju (NDA) team in London. The leader of APC in the UK, Ade Omole, was at the meeting, along with some other stakeholders. A statement by Omole’s assistant, AbdulRasaq Danjuma, said the meeting was to consult with critical APC stakeholders in the UK on Tinubu’s 2023 presidential aspiration. Danjuma quoted Omole as saying: “Asiwaju Bola Ahmed Tinubu is in good health and excellent spirits. “He is in good health, hale and hearty. He will be returning to Nigeria within a few days after necessary consultations here in the UK.”   Governors lead opposition to reworked Electoral Bill     Tax returns: FIRS begins probe of big companies     February… A ruling party’s month of decisions   - Advertisement - According to the statement, the meeting afforded the leadership of the party and NDA to brief Tinubu on progressives activities in the UK. Omole also briefed Tinubu on how patriotic Nigerians in the Diaspora were helping out from their countries of residence to ensure a better Nigeria. Omole said: “We are working round the clock to support the President Muhammadu Buhari APC-led administration and contribute our quota to taking Nigeria to the next level.” The statement said the meeting with the APC national leader espoused the commitment of the Nigerian Diaspora community to nation-building. Also at the meeting were NDA Director-General, Dr. Akin Badeji; Mr Joseph Adebola, Dr Kenny Ojutalayo, Dr Oladapo Habeeb, Mrs Edith Nwachukwu, Hajia Rakiya Abubakar, Dr Ronke Tomori and Mr Lanre Adegun, amongst others.